node.text:
❤️
——
👇🏼 INGREDIENTS:
💥 ASSEMBLY
- 1 1/2 tablespoon melted butter
- 1 slightly beaten egg
- 1/2 cup peanut butter
- 1 1/2 cups almond milk
- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup
- 1 1/2 cups old fashioned rolled oats
- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
- 1/8 teaspoon salt
- 1/4 cup of strawberry or raspberry jam/jelly
——
👇🏼 INSTRUCTIONS:
- Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a large skillet or 8x8 inch baking pan with coconut oil or generously spray with nonstick cooking spray.
- In a large bowl, add in melted and cooled coconut oil, peanut butter, honey, egg and almond milk. Whisk together until well combined and no large lumps of peanut butter remain.
- Fold in oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Pour into prepared skillet/pan and make sure oatmeal is evenly spread out.
- Drop jam by teaspoonful onto oatmeal bake, then very gently swirl.
- Bake for 30-35 minutes until barely golden brown.
- DIG IN WITH A SPOON❗
🎥: @dessertbae
📍: Orlando, Florida

HOMEMADE BISCOFF MAGIC BARS‼️ 😍🪄🔥 Probably the best thing we ever made thus far 🙌🏽😏 #dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS:
- 3/4 cup Lotus Biscoff cookies, crushed
- 1/2 cup unsalted butter , melted
- 1 can condensed milk
- 3/4 cup milk chocolate chips
- 1/2 cup white chocolate chips
- 18 Lotus cookies, evenly put on top
- 1/4 cup Biscoff spread, melted
⁣
✨INSTRUCTIONS:
- Crush your @lotusbiscoffus cookies in a bowl
- Add in the melted butter
- Place mixture in a baking tray and flat the mixture evenly throughout.
- Add and spread condensed milk on top
- Add chocolate & white chocolate chips all over
- Layer your Biscoff Cookies evenly on top
- Bake 320F 30-35 mins or until the edges are golden brown
- Melt and mix Lotus Biscoff spread plus chocolate chips then drizzle all on over the top.
-  Cut in squares & ENJOY! 😉
⁣
🎥: @dessertbae

🥣ONE BOWL PERFECT FUDGE BROWNIES 🍫

1 1/4 cup all purpose flour 
1/3 cup cocoa powder
1 cup butter
1 cup granulated sugar 
3/4 brown sugar 
1 tbsp vanilla 
1 cup chocolate chips 
1/2 cup chopped chocolate 
3 eggs 
1 tsp salt 

Preheat oven to 350F. 
In a large bowl, combine butter and chocolate chips. 
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes and whisk together until silky smooth. 
Add in your sugars, salt, vanilla and eggs and mix well. 
Sift in the flour and cocoa powder then fold until incorporated completely. 
Add in chopped chocolate and pour the mixture into a 8x8 pan lined with parchment paper.
Bake for 40-45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out mostly clean (no wet batter- some crumbs are okay). 
Allow to cool completely before removing from the pan. Brownies should be fudgy in the center once cooled. 

*you may use a 9 x 13 pan if you prefer thinner brownies just be sure to adjust the bake time to 25-30 minutes 🔥🍽💕 #dessertbae

5-INGREDIENT SALTED CARAMEL FUDGE ‼️😍😋 Takes only 5 ingredients & makes a great easy homemade treat 🙌🏽 #dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS💥 
- 1 can condensed milk
- 1/2 cup unsalted butter
- 1 cup light brown sugar
- 1/4 tsp salt (plus extra for sprinkling)
- 1 cup white chocolate

✨INSTRUCTIONS✨
- Line a 9" x 9" pan with foil or parchment paper and mist. with cooking spray
- Place butter, condensed milk, brown sugar, and white chocolate chips in a pan and combine.
- Pour & smooth into the pan topped with some salt then refrigerate for at least an hour.
- Cut into 1" x 1" squares and ENJOY! 🤤
⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
